name: dylan
dataSource: Super enriched combining V6, V7, V8, V10, V11
culturalSignificance: Dylan is a name of Welsh origin, deeply rooted in Welsh mythology. It is associated with Dylan ail Don, a god of the sea in Welsh legend, symbolizing the strength and mystery of the ocean.
modernContext: Dylan remains a popular name in English-speaking countries, often chosen for its poetic and musical associations, partly due to the influence of the famous musician Bob Dylan.
literaryReferences: Dylan Thomas, a renowned Welsh poet, is one of the most notable literary figures with this name.
personality: People named Dylan are often perceived as creative, charismatic, and adventurous, with a strong connection to nature and the arts.
symbolism: The name Dylan symbolizes the power and mystery of the sea, often associated with creativity and depth.
funFact: Bob Dylan, born Robert Zimmerman, chose his stage name in honor of the Welsh poet Dylan Thomas.
